         <abstract>
            <p>How should a plan sponsor set a pension plan's goal? One way is by maximizing expected return for given risk and by fine-tuning the portfolio's risk, possibly including the plan's liabilities as part of the portfolio. A better approach, as the author claims, is to ignore risk and maximize the sponsor's present value, at least as a first cut.</p>
